&lt;b&gt;A worker of the UOC monastery in the Sumy region was injured in a Russian shelling&lt;/b&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On June 2, the Russian army struck with an FPV drone near the Hlynska Pustyn Monastery in the village of Sosnovka, Shostka district, Sumy region. A local resident born in 2003, who worked at the monastery, was injured. He was hospitalized in Hlukhiv with a mine-explosive injury and a fragmentation wound to the chest.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;According to Metropolitan Evlogiy (Gutchenko) of Sumy and Okhtyrka, the Russian shelling of Ukrainian cities once again showed its &quot;true face - the face of evil, ruthlessly bringing death and suffering to the civilian population&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;We will never agree with evil. But we will not break. For God is with us,&quot; Evlogiy said, &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.facebook.com/Evlogiy/posts/pfbid0YHmk4N2sdTD1wNfy4nBYaU8BQiqsjLCD5V9CztD28h62ADFvGcMZnLBQuSHbCFu8l?__cft__[0]=AZXhwwDmc_IA5RBOcrFzN3AZm4_t9-9C-FkGlp8if6CMFWN6pKHQDiudUmKcTi2sIqlgjYFYJl4C85Ag9nnetOAGX1ouQYrSBHphcgNlZikoJH6gp8gP0sxGBB1sA0EH6ICQx4Qsmq4ASVMAuOroqe_5qOLcMipW6P0IsKV5JRSpEpAt1zpJVFDNuZikroY83iY&amp;amp;__tn__=%2CO%2CP-R&quot;&gt;commenting&lt;/a&gt; on the June 3 shelling of Sumy, which killed 4 people and injured 28.&lt;/p&gt;

