&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;There is a heightened alert status around the Radost-Skorbyashchenskiy parish in Minsk.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The entire roadside from the turn from Pritytskogo Street to Yefrosinii Polotskoy Street and up to the Yestoday sports club is completely cleared of cars. Parking lots are blocked off, and &quot;No Stopping&quot; signs have been installed. The parish gates are closed, and a police car is on duty.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Attempts by believers to enter the territory are accompanied by warnings: they are not allowed to linger for long. All - parishioners, staff and clergy - are informed that they will soon have to leave the territory. An inspection of the temple complex premises is expected in connection with the preparation for the visit of Patriarch Kirill, which is &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.me/christianvision/4475&quot;&gt;expected&lt;/a&gt; after 19:00.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Tomorrow is the memory day of St. Euphrosyne of Polotsk, and for the Radost-Skorbyashchenskiy parish this is a special day: one of the temples of the complex is consecrated in her honor, so the holiday is the patronal feast. A solemn all-night vigil was supposed to be served in the small church today. The parish schedule &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.sobor.by/raspisanie.pdf&quot;&gt;indicates&lt;/a&gt; that the start of the service, which takes about two hours, is at 18:00. However, the service is now being hastily moved to an earlier time, since by 19:00 no one should remain on the territory of the temple complex.&lt;/p&gt;

