&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;The Pope asked Putin to take a step towards peace&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Director of the Vatican Press Office, Matteo Bruni, &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.vaticannews.va/ru/pope/news/2025-06/telefonnyj-razgovor-mezhdu-papoy-i-putinym.html&quot;&gt;reported&lt;/a&gt; details about the telephone conversation on June 4 between Pope Leo XIV and the President of Russia, Vladimir Putin.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;During the conversation, in addition to issues of mutual interest, special attention was paid to the situation in Ukraine and peace. The Pope called on Russia to take a step that will contribute to peace, emphasized the importance of dialogue for the implementation of positive contacts between the parties and the search for solutions in the conflict. The discussion was about the humanitarian situation, the need to assist where necessary, the constant efforts to exchange prisoners, and the value of the work being carried out in this direction by Cardinal Zuppi. Pope Leo mentioned Patriarch Kirill, thanking him for the congratulations received at the beginning of his pontificate, and emphasized how common Christian values can be a light to seek peace, protect life and achieve true religious freedom.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

#Vatican #Catholics

